<p class="p">To calculate the mass flow rate
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm10" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mspace width="4pt" class="mspace"/>
     <mi class="mi">M</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> of the multi-phase flow, the density of each phase needs to be obtained. The mass flow rate is calculated in Equation (
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="FD3-sensors-19-02184" class="xref">3</xref>):
 <disp-formula id="FD3-sensors-19-02184" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(3)</label>
  <math id="mm11" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">M</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mi class="mi">A</mi>
     <mo class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi class="mi">α</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">v</mi>
      <mi class="mi">g</mi>
     </msub>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">ρ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">g</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">+</mo>
     <mi class="mi">β</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">v</mi>
      <mi class="mi">w</mi>
     </msub>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">ρ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">w</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">+</mo>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">[</mo>
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
      <mo class="mo">−</mo>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mo class="mo">(</mo>
       <mi class="mi">α</mi>
       <mo class="mo">+</mo>
       <mi class="mi">β</mi>
       <mo class="mo">)</mo>
      </mrow>
      <mo class="mo">]</mo>
     </mrow>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">v</mi>
      <mi class="mi">o</mi>
     </msub>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">ρ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">o</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm12" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">ρ</mi>
     <mi class="mi">g</mi>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm13" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">ρ</mi>
     <mi class="mi">w</mi>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm14" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">ρ</mi>
     <mi class="mi">o</mi>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the density of the gas, water and oil [
 <xref rid="B6-sensors-19-02184" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">6</xref>]. To monitor the volumetric and/or mass flow rate of the multi-phase flow, different technologies have been invented. Over a lifetime of the well each of the parameter can vary. Hence, it is important for the MPFM to measure both density, velocity and phase fraction of the flow.
</p>
